casebody.data:
Parsons, Appellant, v. Denny’s Restaurants, Appellee.

[Cite as Parsons v. Denny’s Restaurants (1989), 46 Ohio St. 3d 602.]

(No. 89-228 — Submitted September 20, 1989 — Decided October 18, 1989.) Inscore, Rinehardt, Whitney & Enderle and Larry L. Inscore, for appellant. Vorys, Sater, Seymour & Pease and Chris J. North, for appellee. John S. Marshall, Spater, Gittes & Terzean, Frederick M. Gittes, Law Offices of Andrew J. Rujicho and Louis A. Jacobs, urging reversal for amicus curiae, Plaintiff Employment Lawyers Assn.

Sua sponte, this cause is dismissed as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Douglas, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur. Holmes and Wright, JJ., dissent, and would affirm.
